The paper deals with the security threat of neural backdoor attacks in deep learning, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper proposes a generative modeling technique to recover the trigger distribution, which involves machine learning and statistical methods, falling under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also develops a defense technique, which involves software engineering principles, falling under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
